author: uli22

text:
Well, there are some expressions that starts with the word "ni" in spanish, like "ni loco" (not even if i'm crazy), "ni borracho" (not even if i'm drunk); "ni papa" (i don't understand anything you said); "ni queriendo" (not even wanting it)... but, basically, that usually means "not even". 
So, in this case, "not even fear can stop me".
